    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/50229607/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/user_normal.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/50229607/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">leonhard</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar40 main-title-rating" title="推荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2012-10-06"
      class="main-meta">2012-10-06 22:38:39</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_5608270_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  断断续续读了一部分，感觉书的内容贯穿了现代传染病学的历史，从巴斯德发现感染的原理开始，若干继承者不断深入探索，直至发现DNA/RNA遗传机制为止。  虽然以1918大流感为题，感觉事实上并不是那次流感的纪实。

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">2有用 / 1没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="review_5608270_full" class="hidden">
            <div id="review_5608270_full_content" class="full-content"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>





